--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bundled third-party binaries (under assets/android/sdk23/)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To emulate Android native libraries, this project bundles a small Android (AOSP)
AArch64 sysroot. These are third-party binaries, redistributed under their
respective licenses:

  - bionic libc.so / libm.so / libdl.so / liblog.so / libstdc++ (libstdcpp.so,
    libcpp.so) — The Android Open Source Project, Apache License 2.0.
  - libcrypto.so / libssl.so — BoringSSL / OpenSSL-derived, under their
    respective (OpenSSL/ISC/SSLeay) licenses.
  - libz.so — zlib, under the zlib license.

These libraries are unmodified system components included only so the emulator
can resolve and execute the standard C runtime an Android native library expects.
All trademarks and copyrights in those components belong to their respective
owners.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Interoperating projects (NOT distributed with this source)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

gonidbg is designed after, and interoperates with, these projects. Their code is
fetched/built or loaded separately, not vendored in this repository:

  - unidbg          (Apache-2.0)  — the design reimplemented here.
  - Unicorn Engine  (GPLv2)       — optional CPU backend, loaded at runtime via
                                    dlopen (kept at a dynamic-library boundary).
  - dynarmic        (0BSD)        — optional CPU backend, fetched + statically
                                    built by build-dynarmic.sh.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example library
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

examples/native/native.so is built from examples/native/native.c (in this repo)
and is original to this project.
